WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:11.500
Clinical research is medical research that involves recruiting people.

00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:22.900
Clinical research helps doctors and researchers learn more
about diseases and improve health services for people in the future.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.900
Types of clinical research include:

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:43.900
1)Epidemiology, which improves the understanding of a
disease by studying patterns, causes, and effects of health and disease in specific groups.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:55.900
2) Behavioral research, which studies human
behavior and how it relates to health and disease.

00:00:35.001 --> 00:01:11.900
3) Health services research, which looks at people's
needs for healthcare services, how people access services and
healthcare providers, how much service costs, and what happens
to patients as a result of this service.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:23.900
4) Clinical trials, which evaluate the effects of a
new intervention like treatment, medicine, medical
device and therapy on health outcomes.
